tLocker uses Secure Boot for platform integrity if the platform is capable of Secure Boot-based integrity validation.","pos":[103942,104061]},{"content":"When disabled","pos":[104122,104135]},{"content":"BitLocker uses legacy platform integrity validation, even on systems that are capable of Secure Boot-based integrity validation.","pos":[104174,104302]},{"content":"Reference","pos":[104340,104349]},{"content":"Secure Boot ensures that the computer's preboot environment loads only firmware that is digitally signed by authorized software publishers.","pos":[104353,104492]},{"content":"Secure Boot also provides more flexibility for managing preboot configurations than BitLocker integrity checks prior to Windows Server 2012 and Windows 8.","pos":[104493,104647]},{"content":"When this policy is enabled and the hardware is capable of using Secure Boot for BitLocker scenarios, the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Use enhanced Boot Configuration Data validation profile<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Group Policy setting is ignored, and Secure Boot verifies BCD settings according to the Secure Boot policy setting, which is configured separately from BitLocker.","pos":[104648,104976]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Warning:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>  Enabling this policy might result in BitLocker recovery when manufacturer-specific firmware is updated.","pos":[104979,105096]},{"content":"If you disable this policy, suspend BitLocker prior to applying firmware updates.","pos":[105097,105178]},{"pos":[105218,105270],"content":"Provide the unique identifiers for your organization"},{"content":"This policy setting is used to establish an identifier that is applied to all drives that are encrypted in your organization.","pos":[105272,105397]},{"content":"Policy description","pos":[105523,105541]},{"content":"With this policy setting, you can associate unique organizational identifiers to a new drive that is enabled with BitLocker.","pos":[105580,105704]},{"content":"Introduced","pos":[105766,105776]},{"content":"Windows Server 2008 R2 and Windows 7","pos":[105815,105851]},{"content":"Drive type","pos":[105912,105922]},{"content":"All drives","pos":[105961,105971]},{"content":"Policy path","pos":[106033,106044]},{"content":"Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\BitLocker Drive Encryption","pos":[106083,106176]},{"content":"Conflicts","pos":[106237,106246]},{"content":"Identification fields are required to manage certificate-based data recovery agents on BitLocker-protected drives.","pos":[106285,106399]},{"content":"BitLocker manages and updates certificate-based data recovery agents only when the identification field is present on a drive and it is identical to the value that is configured on the computer.","pos":[106400,106594]},{"content":"When enabled","pos":[106656,106668]},{"content":"You can configure the identification field on the BitLocker-protected drive and any allowed identification field that is used by your organization.","pos":[106707,106854]},{"content":"When disabled or not configured","pos":[106915,106946]},{"content":"The identification field is not required.","pos":[106985,107026]},{"content":"Reference","pos":[107064,107073]},{"content":"These identifiers are stored as the identification field and the allowed identification field.","pos":[107077,107171]},{"content":"The identification field allows you to associate a unique organizational identifier to BitLocker-protected drives.","pos":[107172,107286]},{"content":"This identifier is automatically added to new BitLocker-protected drives, and it can be updated on existing BitLocker-protected drives by using the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Manage-bde<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/ff829849.aspx)</ept> command-line tool.","pos":[107287,107519]},{"content":"An identification field is required to manage certificate-based data recovery agents on BitLocker-protected drives and for potential updates to the BitLocker To Go Reader.","pos":[107521,107692]},{"content":"BitLocker manages and updates data recovery agents only when the identification field on the drive matches the value that is configured in the identification field.","pos":[107693,107857]},{"content":"In a similar manner, BitLocker updates the BitLocker To Go Reader only when the identification field on the drive matches the value that is configured for the identification field.","pos":[107858,108038]},{"pos":[108040,108167],"content":"For more information about the tool to manage BitLocker, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Manage-bde<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/ff829849.aspx)</ept>."},{"content":"The allowed identification field is used in combination with the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Deny write access to removable drives not protected by BitLocker<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> policy setting to help control the use of removable drives in your organization.","pos":[108169,108383]},{"content":"It is a comma-separated list of identification fields from your organization or external organizations.","pos":[108384,108487]},{"pos":[108489,108649],"content":"You can configure the identification fields on existing drives by using the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Manage-bde<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/ff829849.aspx)</ept> command-line tool."},{"content":"When a BitLocker-protected drive is mounted on another BitLocker-enabled computer, the identification field and the allowed identification field are used to determine whether the drive is from an outside organization.","pos":[108651,108868]},{"content":"Multiple values separated by commas can be entered in the identification and allowed identification fields.","pos":[108870,108977]},{"content":"The identification field can be any value up to 260 characters.","pos":[108978,109041]},{"pos":[109080,109115],"content":"Prevent memory overwrite on restart"},{"content":"This policy setting is used to control whether the computer's memory will be overwritten the next time the computer